lling them in advance about its plans to do the bad thing. There are variat=
ions. One is that if a company has a=C2=A0publicized policy=C2=A0of doing=
=C2=A0good=C2=A0things, and then it does a bad thing (or does=C2=A0not=C2=
=A0do the good things), it will get a lawsuit. And so if you are a company =
with a code of ethics, and an executive does something unethical, you   wil=
l get sued for fraud=C2=A0because you published a code of ethics.=C2=A0=E2=
=80=9CYou said you have a code of ethics, which implied that your executive=
s were ethical, but you neglected to mention that one of them wasn=E2=80=99=
t.=E2=80=9D
