 have quite this culture of =E2=80=9Ceverything is securities fraud=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but you can sort of generalize it. If you are a public c=
ompany and you announce plans to do good things, you will get a lot of scru=
tiny for any failure to live up to those plans. Better not to announce=C2=
=A0them. Here=E2=80=99s  the Financial Times on =E2=80=9Cgreen hushing,=E2=
=80=9D which is a way to avoid accusations of =E2=80=9Cgreenwashing=E2=80=
=9D:

A trend known as =E2=80=9Cgreen hushing=E2=80=9D is growing as companies ar=
e increasingly choosing not to publicise details of their climate targets i=
n an attempt to avoid scrutiny and allegations of greenwashing, a new study=
