10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Reverse meme</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One truly new fact that I have learned about f=
inancial markets in the last two years is that random silly enthusiasm from=
 retail investors on social media can <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMjgva25vd2luZy13aGVuLXRvLXNlbGwtZ2FtZXN0b3Atc3=
RvY2stYXQtdGhlLXRvcC1pcy1pbXBvc3NpYmxlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTgyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJ=
nV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAxOCZ1=
dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB263bec9c" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  save a big company from bankruptcy</a>. You have a somewhat nostalgic con=
sumer-oriented company, it falls on hard times, it has too much debt, thing=
s look grim, short sellers are circling, and then some people on Reddit are=
 like =E2=80=9Chey let=E2=80=99s have some fun and stick it to the short se=
llers,=E2=80=9D it becomes a meme, the stock rallies, the company raises mo=
ney at the new high stock price, it pays off its debts, it expands into non=
-fungible tokens, the retail investors save the day. It is still a little e=
arly to write an ending to this story. =E2=80=9CSaved by retail investors, =
the company becomes a faithful and sensible steward of their capital and pi=
vots to a leading role in the new economy,=E2=80=9D maybe. =E2=80=9CEventua=
lly the company incinerates the Reddit investors=E2=80=99 money the way it =
incinerated previous investors=E2=80=99 money, but everyone has fun along t=
he way,=E2=80=9D also possible.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What about the reverse? Can random silly <em>p=
essimism </em>from retail investors on social media=C2=A0<em>cause=C2=A0</e=
m>a big company to go bankrupt? No, I think is the answer so far, but give =
it time. Here=E2=80=99s a fun New York Times story about how Credit Suisse =
Group AG <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29415403.=
285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMC8xNy9idXNpbmVzcy9jcmVkaXQt=
c3Vpc3NlLW1lbWUtc3RvY2suaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2b20da73" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 became a reverse meme stock</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CCredit Suisse is probably going bankr=
upt.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It was Saturday, Oct. 1, and Jim Lewis, who fr=
equently posts on Twitter under the moniker Wall Street Silver, made that a=
ssertion to his more than 300,000 followers. =E2=80=9CMarkets are saying it=
=E2=80=99s insolvent and probably bust. 2008 moment soon?=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Lewis was among hundreds of people =E2=80=
=94 many of them amateur investors =E2=80=94 who had been speculating about=
 the fate of Credit Suisse, the Swiss bank. It was in the middle of a restr=
ucturing and had become an easy target after decades of scandals, failed at=
tempts at reform and management upheavals. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Reached via private message on Twitter, Mr. Le=
wis said all he had looked at before sending out his tweet was Credit Suiss=
e=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Clow stock price and memes on Reddit.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In another private message on Twitter, Mr. Lew=
is declined to speak further about why he had predicted that Credit Suisse =
would collapse.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe math and evidence is fairly obvio=
us at this point,=E2=80=9D he wrote. =E2=80=9CIf you disagree, the burden i=
s really on you to support that position.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Super. It doesn=E2=80=99t seem to have worked.=
 Credit Suisse=E2=80=99s stock isn=E2=80=99t doing=C2=A0<em>great</em>, but=
 it=E2=80=99s up from where it was after that weekend of rumors. The bank r=
esponded to the rumors by calling clients to say that everything is fine, a=
nd while of course <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjItMTAtMDMvZXZlcnlvbmUtd2FudGVkLXRvLWJ1eS10d2l0dGVyLXdpdGgtZWxvbj9jbXBpZ=
D1CQkQxMDE4MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xl=
dHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMTgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cBb8447fca" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  I quoted the obvious Bagehot line about thi=
s</a>, it more or less did the trick. It helped that the rumors Credit Suis=
se was=C2=A0responding to were from, you know, these guys, as opposed to ru=
mors among informed market participants.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One arguable lesson of the meme-stock story is=
 that fundamental value is a=C2=A0<em>floor=C2=A0</em>on stock prices but n=
ot a=C2=A0<em>cap</em>. If a company has a real business that generates cas=
h flows with a present value of $20 per share, and its stock trades down to=
 $10 per share, then someone will buy it: A private equity firm will buy th=
e whole company for $10 per share, and then just take the $20 per share wor=
th of cash flows for itself. There is a direct catalyst: Through the market=
 for corporate control, the stock can be <em>transformed into its cash flow=
s</em>, so the stock should always be worth at least as much as its cash fl=
ows.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the stock trades up to $40 per share, some =
hedge fund can sell it short, betting that it will return to $20. But that =
doesn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>make it happen.=C2=A0</em>If other people keep buy=
ing, it will stay at $40, or go up more. The hedge fund can=E2=80=99t trans=
form the $40 stock into its $20 of cash flows.<a class=3D"footnote-index" h=
ref=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: i=
nline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9CIn the long run, the stock will be worth only as much as=
 its cash flows,=E2=80=9D one vaguely assumes, but meme-stock mania cast so=
me doubt on that.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgr=
ound-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0<em>How=C2=A0</em>will it be worth only as much as its cash flows=
?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could conclude from this that social-media=
-driven meme-stock campaigns can only work on the long side: Enough people =
with enough dedication can make an arbitrary stock go up as much as they wa=
nt for as long as they want (not investing advice!), but they can=E2=80=99t=
 make it go=C2=A0<em>down=C2=A0</em>as much as they want for as long as the=
y want; eventually a fundamental buyer will step in. Add the generally chee=
ry nature of meme-stock enthusiasm, and it makes sense that meme stocks are=
 the ones that go up.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the exception to this might be a=C2=A0<em>=
bank</em>.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-co=
lor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> A bank is broadly speaking in the business of borrowing short-term to =
lend long-term, and if there is a run on the bank =E2=80=94=C2=A0if people =
all withdraw their short-term funding at once =E2=80=94=C2=A0then it will g=
o bust, even if it is otherwise a good business. Douglas Diamond and Philip=
 Dybvig won the Nobel Memorial Prize in economics this year <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53a=
WtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvRGlhbW9uZCVFMiU4MCU5M0R5YnZpZ19tb2RlbA/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cBa4fa6192" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> for their work</a> on this phenomenon. =E2=
=80=9CA bank run in our model,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnUuZWR1L2Vjb24vZmlsZ=
XMvMjAxMi8wMS9ERDgzanBlLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb52680bb" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 they write</a>,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cis caused by a shift in expectations, which =
could depend on almost anything, consistent with the apparently irrational =
observed behavior of people running on banks.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CAlmost anyt=
hing=E2=80=9D could include social media rumors, why not. And =E2=80=9Cappa=
rently irrational observed behavior=E2=80=9D could be the motto for r/walls=
treetbets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So it is theoretically possible to meme a bank=
 into bankruptcy, in a way that it is not possible to meme, say, Tesla Inc.=
 into bankruptcy.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgr=
ound-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> You get enough people worried, they stop funding the bank, and it blow=
s up, even if its business was otherwise sound. That=C2=A0<a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZWN=
vbmxpYi5vcmcvbGlicmFyeS9CYWdlaG90L2JhZ0xvbS5odG1sP2NoYXB0ZXJfbnVtPTUjYm9vay=
1yZWFkZXI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb142cc92" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">obvious Bagehot line</=
a> is =E2=80=9CEvery banker knows that if he has to prove that he is worthy=
 of credit, however good may be his arguments, in fact his credit is gone.=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of course in modern international banking the =
people you need to get worried are, like, wholesale funding markets and cre=
dit-default swap traders and derivatives counterparties, not retail deposit=
ors or shareholders. The Times:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Amateur traders who gather on soci=
al media can=E2=80=99t trade sophisticated products like credit-default swa=
ps =E2=80=94 products that protect against companies=E2=80=99 reneging on t=
heir debts. But their speculation drove the price of these swaps past level=
s reached during the 2008 financial crisis.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess the next step is for Reddit to <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2ZlYXR1cmVzLzIwMTgtMDUtMDMvaW5zaWRlLXRoZS13=
b3JsZC1zLW1vc3QtZWxpdGUtYW5kLXNlY3JldC10cmFkZXJzLWNsdWI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxODI=
