<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CEverything is securities fraud,=E2=80=
=9D I like to say around here: If a public company does a bad thing, shareh=
olders will sue it for not telling them in advance about its plans to do th=
e bad thing. There are variations. One is that if a company has a=C2=A0<em>=
publicized policy=C2=A0</em>of doing=C2=A0<em>good=C2=A0</em>things, and th=
en it does a bad thing (or does=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>do the good things),=
 it will get a lawsuit. And so if you are a company with a code of ethics, =
and an executive does something unethical, you <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
