=C2=A0very much without giving legal advice! =E2=80=94=C2=A0that the second=
 approach, empirically,=C2=A0<em>works:=C2=A0</em>US regulators abstractly,=
 and sometimes concretely, do not like the idea that decentralized finance =
is insulated from regulatory oversight, but in practice it seems to be kind=
 of true.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-col=
or: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The exchanges that are most subject to regulation are the ones th=
at pick up the phone when regulators call. If you don=E2=80=99t have a phon=
e number, they can never call you.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway I guess a third approach is: Set up a c=
entralized exchange, form like 100 corporations in different countries, and=
=C2=A0<em>don=E2=80=99t tell anyone which one runs the exchange?=C2=A0</em>=
That is extremely not legal advice but <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vaW52ZX=
N0aWdhdGVzL3NwZWNpYWwtcmVwb3J0L2ZpbnRlY2gtY3J5cHRvLWJpbmFuY2Utemhhby8/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB2112ddb7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> here=E2=80=99s Reuters on Binance</a=
>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Described on its website as an =E2=80=9Cecosys=
tem=E2=80=9D with over 120 million users, Binance has set up at least 73 co=
mpanies across the world, according to corporate filings and company organi=
sation charts. [Founder Changpeng =E2=80=9CCZ=E2=80=9D] Zhao owns or partly=
 controls at least 59. He declines to give details of the location or entit=
y behind the main exchange, which makes money by charging fees on crypto tr=
ades. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One example of his oversight came in early 202=
0. A London-based payments partner called Checkout.com asked Binance to sta=
te on its website that one of Binance=E2=80=99s British units =E2=80=9Cshal=
l be responsible for transactions=E2=80=9D conducted using traditional mone=
y. A Checkout.com spokesperson said the request was =E2=80=9Ccompletely sta=
ndard across the payments and commerce worlds.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Binance employee raised a warning about the =
requested statement in a message exchange that included Zhao and other exec=
utives. The employee cautioned that the statement would leave a =E2=80=9Cpa=
per trail=E2=80=9D linking the British unit to the main exchange, which Bin=
ance has shielded from global regulators by not providing details of its lo=
cation.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You know US regulators won=E2=80=99t like this=
, but you can distract them by giving them a US entity to chew on:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Harry Zhou ran a U.S. crypto trading firm that=
 Binance had invested in. He sent a proposal to a Binance executives=E2=80=
=99 message group to address =E2=80=9CBinance-specific risks in the US.=E2=
=80=9D Zhou suggested what he described as a =E2=80=9CTai-Chi entity,=E2=80=
=9D a reference to a martial art with defensive virtues.=C2=A0...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Binance would restrict U.S. customers=E2=80=99=
 access to the main platform, the presentation said. But Binance would enab=
le =E2=80=9Cstrategic=E2=80=9D use of virtual private networks, which obscu=
re the location of internet users, to =E2=80=9Cminimize economic impact=E2=
=80=9D of the changes. This would leave a loophole: U.S.-based traders woul=
d still be able to access the main exchange, with its greater liquidity and=
 broader range of products, by using a VPN connection.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Zhou=E2=80=99s presentation explained the burd=
ens of the main exchange being regulated: =E2=80=9Cactive outreach to regul=
ators can result in lengthy inquiries and requests for excessive disclosure=
s; settlement costs can be substantial.=E2=80=9D But the Tai Chi structure =
would =E2=80=9Cinsulate Binance from legacy and future liabilities=E2=80=9D=
 and =E2=80=9Cretard and resolve built-up enforcement tensions.=E2=80=9D Th=
e Tai Chi entity =E2=80=93 and not Binance itself =E2=80=93 would become =
=E2=80=9Cthe target=E2=80=9D of U.S. authorities.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/29415403.285506/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmluYW5jZS5jb20vZW4vYmxv=
Zy9mcm9tLWN6L291ci1yZXNwb25zZS10by10aGUtbGF0ZXN0LXJldXRlcnMtc3RvcnktMzQyOTA=
1NTQ4MTQ1Mjk4NTA3OD9yZWY9QVpUS1o5WFMmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1CaW5hbmNlVHdpdHRlciZ1dG=
1fbWVkaXVtPUdsb2JhbFNvY2lhbCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249R2xvYmFsU29jaWFs/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBb78b2e17" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;">Zhao=E2=80=99s=C2=A0response to the article<=
/a>, which notes that the =E2=80=9CTai Chi=E2=80=9D idea was never adopted,=
 and =E2=80=9CEventually, Binance.US was set up based on advice from leadin=
g US law firms. Today, Binance.US is licensed to operate across the United =
States, and operates independently from Binance.com.=E2=80=9D It also notes=
 that, generally, Binance has a lot of compliance and know-your-customer ch=
ecks and works with regulators to stop crime. And:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Why Don=E2=80=99t We Share the Location of Our=
 Offices?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is actually similar to the argument about=
 why I don=E2=80=99t want my family to be in the media. Over the last two y=
ears, we have worked with global law enforcement to seize assets of countle=
ss criminal organizations across the globe, which has directly resulted in =
cleaner crypto markets. So, we are careful when disclosing office locations=
, wearing Binance branding, or representing ourselves as Binance employees =
for security purposes. I want to keep our employees safe. However, regulato=
rs in each jurisdiction where we operate have our local address and contact=
 details on file and we have announced major offices in Paris and Dubai. We=
 have also set up a special part of the Binance website specifically for La=
w Enforcement.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is something very <em>crypto=C2=A0</em>a=
bout this. If you built a bond trading platform and went out to asset manag=
ers to sign them up, they would ask you questions like =E2=80=9Cwhere is th=
is platform incorporated?=E2=80=9D And if you said =E2=80=9Coh that=E2=80=
=99s a secret,=E2=80=9D that would be a=C2=A0<em>gigantic red flag and no o=
ne would sign up</em>. In crypto, though, permissionless anonymous decentra=
lized finance is a <em>goal</em>, and =E2=80=9Cwe don=E2=80=99t want to get=
 any regulated legal entities involved in our exchange=E2=80=9D is a natura=
l thing to say. Sometimes this involves actual DeFi =E2=80=94=C2=A0exchange=
s that are open-source smart-contract protocols running on a blockchain =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0but sometimes it involves centralized exchanges that are <em>co=
mpanies</em>, but <em>secret</em>.</p>
